Please run the following steps : 
  1.install node.js, 
  install mysql and create user - admin and password - password (Or change server.js file accordingly)
  2.node server.js                    --- server initial setup
  3.npm install ejs --save
  4 npm install express --save
  5.npm install body-parser --save
  (Install any other dependancy if needed be )
  6.node app.js                       --- webserver for this app 
  7.point your browser to http://127.0.0.1:8080/
  8.Be online! Chartjs doesnot run in offline mode as its pointed to their repo. 
                                You can also create a local repo in case you need offline access
  
  
